Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 31
Edition:
Quote: <i>crayfish</i> a crawler or contemptible schemer; from army WWI; eg `That ruddy Miller's the crayfish round here. Next time one of us is done, he cops a bunch of fives.'
